SIMPLE: subaxillary
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subaxillary
<hw>Sub*ax"il*la*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Situated under the axilla, or armpit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Placed under the axil, or angle
formed by the branch of a plant with the stem, or a leaf with the
branch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subbasal</ent>⟦br⟧
